data.text:
Portugal has seen its doctors increasingly leave for better paid positions in the rest of Europe—leaving one in 10 citizens with no GP. Sally Howard reports

We need to prioritise the lives and health of women and children, not repressive policies that benefit no one and cause serious harm to many
